->status and then headers and then body
->if there is no body  then use build() instead of body
return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.ok).headers(headers).body("msg");
->1xx for informational
2xx for success (220 - > success , 201 -> created , 202 -> accepted , 204 -> no content , 206 -> partially accept)
3xx for redirection (
4xx for validation error
5xx for server error
status codes are in docs